      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Potential deep dives and non-functional requirements:\n\n1. How to handle users following a large number of users:\n\nThere is an issue in this as multiple requests are going to be made to DB for a single request to complete. So it will be let's say \n1000s of requests to be handled for one request to pass. This is k/a fanout problem.\n\nThe solution is to keep precomputed feeds. Find all the followings of the user who is posting and then push in the precomputed feeds.\nPrecomputed feed:\n",
