      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2. Handle users with large #followers:\n\nIf we simply go and update the precomputed feeds. The DB will get overwhelmed to over a million writes. \nIf we use queue also in between then also our workers needs to do a lot of work\n\nThe solution is writes will happen through queue only, but we will keep a flag in the Follow table as precomputed or not. If not\nthen we will rely on basic solution to read both tables of follow and Posts. \nSo we are going with hybrid approach here. \n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2. Handle users with large #followers:\n\nIf we simply go and update the precomputed feeds. The DB will get overwhelmed to over a million writes. \nIf we use queue also in between then also our workers needs to do a lot of work\n\nThe solution is writes will happen through queue only, but we will keep a flag in the Follow table as precomputed or not. If not\nthen we will rely on basic solution to read both tables of follow and Posts. \nSo we are going with hybrid approach here. \n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
